"    This scatter plot shows the levels of ZAP-70 expression, as measured by flow cytometry, in lymphocytes from 56 patients with chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL). Also shown for each patient is the mutational status of the variable region of the immunoglobulin heavy chain. Open circles represent subjects with mutated Vh genes, while the closed circles are from patients with unmutated Vh genes. In this study, the two groups were almost completely separable when the threshold for categorizing ZAP-70 positivity was set at 20 percent (dashed line).",
